As demonstrated by the stepwise selection using AIC above with a model containing the max_sd and max_mr variables added to the variables previously determined to be the most important predictors of maximum daily infection rate, adding max_mr to the model does result in a lower AIC (1303.66) as compared to the one generated using log(density) and log(gdp_capita) (1313.6). Additionally, the pseudo-R^2 values are also increased in the model using max_mr as an additional predictor variable.
